      },
    ],
  },
  en: {
    title: 'Regenerative Medicine Unit of Dénia (UMERED)',
    intro: `<p>In this Unit we have focused medical and aesthetic treatments for Regenerative purposes.</p>
<p><strong class="font-bold text-zeniaMarronOscuro">Aesthetic Medicine:</strong></p>
<ul class="list-none space-y-2">
  <li>&#9679; <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">Platelet-Rich Plasma</strong>, for facial, neck and décolleté regeneration, as well as to improve scars, keloids and blemishes.</li>
  <li>&#9679; <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">Exosomes:</strong> nanoparticles produced by cells that act as intercellular messengers, containing <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">DNA and RNA</strong> and used to facilitate communication between cells. Their goal in aesthetic medicine is to <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">improve skin and tissue quality</strong> by promoting their regeneration.</li>
  <li>&#9679; <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">Polynucleotides (PDRN):</strong> DNA fragments that induce a non-inflammatory <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">tissue regeneration</strong> response and promote the <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">synthesis of hyaluronic acid, collagen and elastin</strong>, achieving skin rejuvenation. They have an <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">antioxidant effect</strong> that counteracts the harmful effects of free radicals on the skin. They have both facial and body applications.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong class="font-bold text-zeniaMarronOscuro">General Medicine and Traumatology:</strong> At <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">UMERED</strong> we carry out a <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">protocol aimed at regenerating tendon and osteoarticular injuries</strong>, with <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">ultrasound-guided</strong> injections, with the aim of regenerating injuries and improving pain.</p>`,
