      {
        summary: 'Ultrasound-Guided PRP Injection',
        title: 'ULTRASOUND-GUIDED PRP INJECTION',
        body: `<p>One of the specialties of our <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">Regenerative Medicine Unit of Denia (UMERED)</strong> is to help the rapid recovery of patients with acute, subacute or chronic pain due to <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">osteoarticular injuries</strong> who have not achieved fully satisfactory results with conventional treatments.</p>
<p><strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">PRP (Platelet-Rich Plasma)</strong> is a treatment indicated for a large number of <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">degenerative injuries, acute or chronic tendinitis, osteoarthritis, ligament tears</strong> and all types of injuries where <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">tissue regeneration</strong> is needed.</p>
<p>At our clinic this procedure is performed supervised with <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">ultrasound imaging</strong>, ensuring we inject in the correct location without touching other structures with the needle.</p>
<p>We use <strong class="font-bold underline text-zeniaRosaOscuro">high-end technology</strong> that ensures better results to regenerate damaged structures in a short time with maximum guarantees.</p>
<p>The number of sessions will depend on each specific injury. For this, we carry out continuous assessment in all cases to obtain satisfactory results.</p>
<p class="font-semibold text-zeniaRosaOscuro">Don't give up on a pain-free life. Ask us how we can help you.</p>`,
